&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Practice Assist?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Practice Assist is an innovative service which involves a central hub, based in Southall, that supports GP practices across the country by providing access to telephone appointments for patients. This will free up GP time within the practices to support those patients that really need to be seen face-to-face.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Run by Practice Plus Group, the UK&#39;s largest independent provider of NHS services, we are seeking experienced GPs to join our hard working Practice Assist team on a self-employed basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role involves carrying out telephone consultations for patients across the country, with read / write access to their medical records so a full consultation can be carried out and documented. This work is carried out from the hub, and there is also a potential for home working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be part of a close working team of GPs, working on a self-employed or bank basis with the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Information&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that offers of employment are subject to receipt of satisfactory references and a DBS check.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Practice Plus Group, we actively promote diversity and equal opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have the right to work in the EU.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;d like to learn more, arrange an informal visit to the service or have any questions please contact Karla Smith – karla.smith@careuk.com / 07918 766 170&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
